ce:section.ce:para:
The optical responses of the CPDs conjugates in different pH solutions were tested. As shown in Fig. 4
                        , the absorbance intensity and fluorescence intensity of PPa-CPD1 and PPa-CPD2 changed when measured in solutions with different pH values. The absorbance intensity of PPa-CPD1 and PPa-CPD2 were the highest at pH 4.0 and pH 5.0 respectively, while the fluorescence intensity of PPa-CPD1 and PPa-CPD2 were both at pH 4.0 (Table 1
                        ). The results showed that PPa-CPD1 and PPa-CPD2 had the pH response and stronger ability to absorb light and produce fluorescence in an acidic environment, which may improve the specific treatment and bioimaging of tumor because the microenvironment of tumor tissue and cells is somewhat acidic. The pH response of the CPDs conjugates was somewhat similar to the results described by Huo et al. [45].
